Job Description:
AEONMALL Vietnam Co., Ltd. is a core enterprise of AEON group, specializing in shopping mall development and business operation. Based on the basic philosophy “Customer first”, we are continuing our efforts to create malls that enhance the quality of life, stimulate local economic activities, and contribute to community life and culture.
Because of business demand, we are in need of recruiting 01 Event Marketing Senior Executive in AEON MALL Binh Tan.

+ Work location: AEON MALL Binh Tan Phu - No.01, Street 17A, Quarter 11, An Lac Ward, HCMC.
+ Working time: On average 5 days/ week and in shift (A shift 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM & C shift 1:30 PM – 10:30 PM, about 5-7 C shifts/ month), OFF days not fixed on weekends, and required to work on some public holidays.
+ Report to: Deputy Manager

Job summary:
Plan, develop, and evaluate offline marketing campaigns related to various fields: POSM, decoration, activation, event, advertisement and promotion to attract customers and boost sales for tenants. Cooperate with outside partners to promote CSR, CSV, SDGs activities to build brand awareness and positioning.

Detailed job description:
1. Make periodical marketing plan/activities to attract customers to increase tenant sales and promote
customer interaction. Manage and control budget (20%);
2. Cooperate with outside partner to promote CSR, CSV, SDGs activities in order to contribute to community
and build brand awareness / positioning (15%);
3. Cooperate with Sales team to plan and implement boost sales activities to push sales for Tenants (15%);
4. Manage tasks of event team to ensure the team work, make the discipline, create the internal code of
conduct. By that, innovate a standard of action for any member to follow, act and check (15%);
5. Cooperate with agencies, vendors to run campaign smoothly and successfully, guarantee the affect
of campaign related to quality, budget, customer satisfaction and process internal document procedure efficiently (10%);
6. Analyze and evaluate the effectiveness of each campaign, methods, costs, and results to improve campaign performance (10%);
7. Make quality and on time report: campaign report, monthly report and other reports as assigned (10%);
8. Other tasks as assigned by supervisors (5%).

